title: H.S. football: Defensive Player of the Year Watch
text:
H.S. football: Defensive Player of the Year Watch October 19, 2015 Last updated: Monday, October 19, 2015, 1:20 AM The Record 
Defensive Player of the Year watch 
Jordan Fuller, NV/Old Tappan, sr. CB 
Played a key role in shutting down Pascack Valley's passing game in a win. Intercepted his second pass of the season and returned it 49 yards for a TD. 
Rashan Gary, Paramus Catholic, sr. DL 
Forced a fumble, recovered a fumble, defended a pass and recorded three tackles for losses in just three quarters of action during a victory over Friendship Academy. Has four sacks and eight tackles for losses in past three games. 
Joey Kenny, Wayne Hills, sr. LB 
Recorded two sacks and two tackles for losses in a win over Teaneck. The Patriots' defensive leader has 63 tackles, including eight for losses and five sacks, in six games. 
Josh Paez, Wood-Ridge, sr. LB 
Had 10 tackles, a sack and an interception in a defeat of Bogota. Leads the Blue Devils with 65 tackles through six games. 
Jaysen Thompson, Hackensack, sr. LB 
Recorded 12 tackles, including a quartet for losses, in the Comets' victory over Fair Lawn. The Comets' top tackler has 51 overall (16 for losses) in five games. Â© 2015 North Jersey Media Group Tags:
